<br>
In my opinion, as a magician in non-raiding guild:<br>
<br>
General:<br>
Run 3<br>
By far the best bang for the buck of an AA's<br>
<br>
Regen 3<br>
Here is where the debate can start.  I see some people who buy stamina, some who buy innate intelligence, and some who buy magic resistance, and some metabolism.<br>
<br>
Stamina is *incredibly* bad.  6 stamina for a magician with durability 3 come out to roughly 17 hit points, and anyone who would trade 17 max hit points over 30 hit points/minute is crazy.<br>
<br>
Metabolism is nice if you eat a lot of stat food and own a chain bridle.  I own a chain bridle and just stuff myself with regular food before eating the good stuff, its annoying, but I cannot bring myself to spend 3 AA's here while I still have good stuff to buy.<br>
<br>
Intelligence is pretty bad, unless you have innate enligthment/planar power maxed, and regeneration is much harder to raise and much more useful.<br>
<br>
Magic Resistance is good on a PvP server, but even then I play on RZ and find regen more useful.<br>
<br>
Archetypes:<br>
Here are where mages get the best AA abilities, and is where you should focus on spending the bulk of your points.<br>
<br>
1) Spell Casting Mastery:  Not enough has been said about how good this skill is, BUY IT BUY IT to level 3 before even thinking of buying anything else, exceptions if you are on a PvP server where crits are marginally more useful.<br>
<br>
2) Spell Casting Fury:  This is a unique AA in that its only good at level 3, however at level 3 it is very very useful.  Buy this after maxing mastery.<br>
<br>
3) Spell Casting Subtlety:  I have only FT 8, and yet before I bought this I found that I could not spend my mana fast enough nuking in a regular experience group if a warrior was tanking, after I bought it I can pretty much stay below FM the entire time and nuke without fear of aggro.  Don't buy this thinking it will allow you to chain nuke impunitely, but this is a great skill on raids.<br>
<br>
4) Mental Clarity:  Level 1 is a great great bargain and should be bought asap, after that the diminish returns are harsh.  Buy one then hold onto better things.<br>
<br>
5) Durability:  This is perhaps the most overbought AA bar none.  It is a *very* good AA ability, and extra hit points are a great thing to have, but whenever I browse Magelo's and see Necromancers (they are the biggest offenders) with maxed Durability but unmaxed mastery Baby Jesus cries.  This is a very good AA, but it is mainly used to 'inflate' your magelo, and it shouldn't be bought until more important AA's are maxed (imho anyway)<br>
<br>
6) Agility:  I haven't bought this yet, but I heard good things about it, will probably buy it sooner or later.<br>
<br>
Class:<br>
<br>
Magicians have the worst class skills bar none.  I suggest you mostly ignore those, unless you wish to go down the pet cannibalization root.  However, I predict it will be *significantly* nerfed soon, so keep that in mind.<br>
<br>
Pet Discipline is nice, but pet hold is superior in all but a few situations (soloing in BoT), frenzied burnout is great on a PvP server and when charming elementals in BoT, although again it probably should/will be nerfed, elemental forms are totally useless other than as toys, and quick summoning/elemental pact are good if you wish to go down the pet-canni route.<br>
<br>
PoP AA:<br>
Innate Enlightment/Power:  I don't have much experience with those, however I would be interested to hear if there is a diminishing return for stats over 255 for intelligence to mana, like there is for stamina to hitpoints.  My gut feeling is that they are worth buying once you bought all the good stuff.<br>
<br>
PoP Class:<br>
Here we get two wonderful AA's:<br>
Pet Hold:  Max it asap, this is great for the regular mage, and great for pet canni... truly a fantastic convenience.<br>
<br>
Host of Elements:  Max it, great for aggro-free damage, and 180 or so extra DPS on raids for 30 seconds is wonderful.  A word of warning, the push from those pets is brutal, so be careful when using it.<br>
<br>
To Conclude, here is my take on the order AA's should be purchased on (and in my opinion, levels &gt; all except SCM3, so get SCM3, then ding to 65, then get your other AA's, expecially if you can get runes).<br>
<br>
(This path is optimized without including pet Cannibalization)<br>
Run 3<br>
Regen 3<br>
SCM 3<br>
SCF 3<br>
FoM 2<br>
MC 1<br>
Suspended Minion 2<br>
Subtlety 3<br>
Host of Elements 3<br>
FoM 3<br>
(*I am here ATM*)<br>
Durability 3<br>
MC 2, 3<br>
Then I haven't planned yet :P<br>
